To meet new requirements originating from Privacy legislation and regulatory bodies in the financial services sector, my company has decided to introduce a Data Classification policy. The policy will specify the levels of sensitivity of various types of data/documents and the access controls required for each level. Confluence can already support this using Space and Page level security controls. However, we believe it would be much more convenient to have the ability to apply (pre-defined) access controls according to a document's data classification within a single space. I think this would be similar to the "issue level" security in JIRA.

