Currently, if I want to limit a search to labelled content objects that use a particular label I must use this search prefix 'labelText:keyword' .

The search prefix will not work if you do change the capitalisation: e.g. labeltext. 

Can we make this prefix a bit simpler, and easier to use by:

1. Ensuring that search syntax is not cap sensitive;
2. Using the prefix 'label:' rather than 'labelText:' 

Cap sensitivity seems overly restrictive, and not user friendly.

label: seems more intuitive than labeltext:

